<p>I am using Elysium Extra.</p>  <p>I am using their TextBoxExtended as follows:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;extra:TextBoxExtended Margin="0,0,0,10" Style="{StaticResource MultiLineTextBoxExtendedStyle}" Text="{Binding HeroesDBDescription}" Watermark="Long Description..." HorizontalContentAlignment="Center"/&gt; </code></pre>  <p>I have a datagrid displayed along with this, defined as follows:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;DataGrid extra:UIElementAttached.IsBubblingMouseWheelEvents="True" ItemsSource="{Binding HeroesDBHeroes}" IsTabStop="False" KeyboardNavigation.TabNavigation="None" Grid.Row="1" IsReadOnly="True" Background="Transparent" AlternatingRowBackground="#BF2B2B2B" AlternationCount="2"&gt;     ... &lt;/DataGrid&gt; </code></pre>  <p>When I hit enter with keyboard focus inside the TextBoxExtended, it is meant to take a new line. However, it does not and instead sends keyboard focus to the cell in first column, last row of the datagrid.</p>  <p>If I hold Shift and enter, it takes a new line as normal. If the DG has no rows, it takes a new line as normal. </p>